editions.flavor: Bant mages still call to the heavens for aid, but angels are not the only ones who answer.

name: War Horn
text: Attacking creatures you control get +1/+0.

editions.flavor: The reverberations course through the warriors' veins, beat with their hearts, and pound with their footfalls as they charge into battle.

name: Warleader's Helix
text: Warleader's Helix deals 4 damage to target creature or player and you gain 4 life.

editions.flavor:
"There is no time to remedy our enemies' ignorance. Blast it out of them."
—Aurelia

name: Warlord's Axe
text:
Equipped creature gets +3/+1.
Equip {4} ({4}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

editions.flavor: To split wood with it would be sacrilege. This tool has but one purpose, and that is war.

text: Trample

name: Warmind Infantry
text: Battalion — Whenever Warmind Infantry and at least two other creatures attack, Warmind Infantry gets +2/+0 until end of turn.

editions.flavor: Before Aurelia denounced Niv-Mizzet, the two guilds had collaborated on the Warmind Initiative in pursuit of the ultimate soldier.

name: Warmonger
text: {2}: Warmonger deals 1 damage to each creature without flying and each player. Any player may activate this ability.

editions.flavor: Funny how money and war travel so well together.

name: Warmonger Hellkite
text:
Flying
All creatures attack each combat if able.
{1}{R}: Attacking creatures get +1/+0 until end of turn.

editions.flavor: Its wings beat to the howls of war and fan the fires of rage.

name: Warmonger's Chariot
text:
Equipped creature gets +2/+2.
As long as equipped creature has defender, it can attack as though it didn't have defender.
Equip {3} ({3}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

editions.flavor: The best defense is a good offense.
The best defense is a good offense.

name: Warmth
text: Whenever an opponent casts a red spell, you gain 2 life.

editions.flavor:
"Flame grows gentle with but a little distance."
—Orim, Samite healer

name: War-Name Aspirant
text:
Raid — War-Name Aspirant enters the battlefield with a +1/+1 counter on it if you attacked with a creature this turn.
War-Name Aspirant can't be blocked by creatures with power 1 or less.

editions.flavor: No battle means more to a Mardu warrior than the one that earns her war name.

name: Warning
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt by target attacking creature this turn.

editions.flavor:
"The folk of the Karplusan Mountains are impossible to ambush."
—Lovisa Coldeyes,
Balduvian Chieftain

name: War Oracle
text:
Lifelink (Damage dealt by this creature also causes you to gain that much life.)
Renown 1 (When this creature deals combat damage to a player, if it isn't renowned, put a +1/+1 counter on it and it becomes renowned.)

editions.flavor: "When you are felled by my mace, you shall know it was divine fate."

name: Warp Artifact
text:
Enchant artifact
At the beginning of the upkeep of enchanted artifact's controller, Warp Artifact deals 1 damage to that player.

name: Warpath
text: Warpath deals 3 damage to each blocking creature and each blocked creature.

editions.flavor: Cho-Manno had never seen Mercadia City's forces fight so well. The magistrate must have hired a new hero.
The battle was over, but the carnage continued for days.
Ghouls are often found skulking on the fringes of great battles, showing themselves only to snatch the wounded and weak, dragging their victims screaming into the shadows.

name: Warped Devotion
text: Whenever a permanent is returned to a player's hand, that player discards a card.

editions.flavor:
"Before the glory of Yawgmoth, yes, even this makes sense."
—Urza, to Gerrard

"The spirit of the devout is easily crushed by the loss of hope."
—Fallen angel

name: Warped Landscape
text:
{T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Warped Landscape: Search your library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.

editions.flavor: Each cryptolith twists the plane's mana, bending its flow to a singular purpose.
